Payment Methods and Financial Behavior: A Comparison of Online and Cash Transactions among University Students.

This research investigates how different payment methods (cash vs. digital payments) influence university students' financial behaviour and spending habits. We are exploring whether using cash helps students maintain better control over their spending compared to digital payment methods and how different types of transactions affect financial management among university students.
Your participation in this survey will help us understand these important financial behaviours in our increasingly digital world. The survey takes approximately 5-10 minutes to complete and asks about your payment preferences, spending habits, and financial management experiences.

By proceeding with this survey, you confirm that you are 18 years or older, currently a university student, understand that participation is voluntary and you can withdraw at any time, and consent to your anonymous responses being used for academic research purposes.
